// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_RogToHero_SL6-7_Task_09 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - ScryingGlyph 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2584599317" "<color orange>You look down upon the stone tablet and its strange runes. After a few moments you realize that each rune is carved into a small block of stone and can be depressed, almost like a keypad. The proper sequence should deactivate the scrying glyph used by the Mu Adepts to monitor the ruins. But which runes are used in the combination?</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P4029660121" "Examine the runes more closely"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1648910353" "<color orange>After examining the runes more closely you can see that four appear to be free of dust. Those must be the ones to depress, but in what order?<br><br>You remember part of Desdemona's message. Of course! She hid the combination encoded within.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P2359111261" "Recall Desdemona's message"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P2340187069" "<color orange>You recall Desdemona's message.</color><br><br>"{HeroName}, I, know we haven't seen <i>eye</i> to eye in the past, but now I have an offer of <i>power</i> that I would like you to <i>take</i>. Refuse and I shall take no offense. Accept and this is only the <i>beginning</i> of what we can accomplish.""
// Answer Text :
"P2528096955" "Press the runes for Eye, Power, Take, and Beginning."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P2110611005" "<color orange>You press the runes and they light up in sequence. When you press the <i>Take</i> rune you can feel magical energy starting to shift through the air around you. All that remains is to press the rune of beginning.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P2588374408" "Press the rune of Beginning."
// Page InformationPage4 Text :
"P799629958" "<color orange>As you depress the stone key light shoots out of the four runes on the tablet and the air shudders with magical power. And then, just as suddenly, the magical power is gone, along with the glowing of the runes. You've done it! You've deactivated the Scrying Glyphs!</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1517400020" "Leave"
// Page InformationPage5 Text :
"P2703085863" "<color orange>Just as you are turning to leave you hear a vocal alarm raised by the Arachnos forces inside the ruins. Apparently they too felt the magic of the Scrying Glyphs dissipate and they are headed your way!</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P2311663164" "Leave quickly!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3831843201" "If Desdemona can be trusted then this could be a big break for you. Arachnos, after all, has an entire country backing them financially, and rubbing some salt in their wounds is modus operandi as long as the Arbiters don't get bitten. Nobody will hold it against you if you trounce them for your own gain."
// AcceptString :
"P274607352" "Infiltrate the ruins and get Desdemona out"
// SendOffString :
"P1796464019" "All you have to do is walk into the Arachnos occupied ruins with Desdemona's invitation, block the scrying glyphs, dispell the vault wards and then walk Desdemona and the loot right out the front."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3053398792" "Help Desdemona rob Arachnos"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1390347281" "From the sound of it, this offer isn't going to be around forever. If you were in Desdemona's position you wouldn't send a message like that and wait around to be betrayed yourself. If you want a cut of the profit, you'd better get a move on and find those ruins."
// TaskTitle :
"P3268855403" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Desdemona's Daring Double Cross</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Hero Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P3216966672" "Ancient ruins being picked over by Arachnos for mystical secrets, check. Dastardly plan to rob them of all their hard work, check. Getting away with it and leaving them none the wiser, unlikely, but worth a shot."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P723814139" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Desdemona's Daring Double Cross</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You feel pretty good. Sure, things didn't go exactly according to plan, but Desdemona got out alive with some important magical knowledge and you got to pull the wool over Arachnos's eyes. You didn't get paid in cold hard cash, but sometimes the little pleasures in life are worth it."
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2315306244" "Scrying Glyph"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P4165056537" "This tablet is covered with ancient runes. Touching the runes in specific sequences will trigger the tablet's magic."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptGlyphDeactivated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P1230858323" "Deactivate the Scrying Glyph"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P3185752392" "<shout>The Mu Adepts report that the Glyphs have been broken!"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P1214344819" "{HeroName}! What are you up to?"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P443161034" "Fortunata Scryer"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P2301231670" "<shout>{HeroName} is the betrayer! All Arachnos forces, kill {HeroName}!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P736962725" "You were a fool to try and betray us, {HeroName}... But now I see that Desdemona is the true traitor. She shall be dealt with in kind!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptAuthoritiesWaveOne 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P847864662" "Defeat the Fortunata Scryer"

